			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Summary&nbsp;<br />
	The Email Marketing Specialist is responsible for coordinating all tactical elements of the email marketing campaigns.&nbsp; This includes receiving creative and data files, requesting approvals, executing tests, QA, and sends, and reporting and analyzing on the overall email campaign results.</p>
<p>
	Essential Duties and Responsibilities<br />
	&bull; Ensures timely execution of email campaigns which involves coordinating with various areas of the marketing and creative department.&nbsp;<br />
	&bull; Performs final test and quality assurance check on all emails for compatibility with web browsers and email clients; ensuring all links, images, subject lines and list segments are correct.&nbsp; Corrects any identified errors with assistance form the creative department or the email vendor.&nbsp;<br />
	&bull; Uses email vendor&rsquo;s reporting system to continually monitor and track email key performance indicators by segment and campaign.&nbsp; Summarizes and shares the results with the marking management team monthly.&nbsp;<br />
	&bull; Maintains the email portfolio book which includes samples of all current and previous email campaigns.<br />
	&bull; Participates in weekly meetings involving the database team, creative, and priority to manage mailing schedules.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Position Requirements<br />
	Education:<br />
	&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree preferred<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Knowledge &amp; Experience:<br />
	&bull; One year of professional work experience preferred, especially in the areas of digital/online marketing (email, web, or social), marketing administration, marketing coordination, or marketing automation.<br />
	&bull; Proficient computer skills including knowledge of Excel, Word, PowerPoint, and various social media<br />
	&bull; Experience with Exact Target or similar ESP is a plus.<br />
	&bull; Proficient in Microsoft Outlook, Word, Excel, PowerPoint<br />
	&bull; Basic knowledge of HTML is a plus<br />
	&bull; Working knowledge and understanding of email marketing best practices<br />
	&bull; Working knowledge of email metrics (open rates, CTR, deliverability, opt outs)<br />
	&bull; Ability to identify data anomalies and potential errors that require additional investigation<br />
	&bull; Knowledge of database/email marketing concepts<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Personal Attributes:<br />
	&bull; Ability to successfully organize and prioritize multiple email template projects in a deadline-driven environment<br />
	&bull; Extreme attention to detail<br />
	&bull; Excellent communication (written and verbal), organization, and customer service skills<br />
	&bull; Ability to work and interact smoothly and effectively in a team-oriented environment.<br />
	&bull; Impeccable eye for detail, strong organization skills, and ability to meet tight deadlines<br />
	&bull; Dedication to meeting the expectations and requirements of members, partners, and co-workers<br />
	&bull; Able to operate independently and with minimal supervision<br />
	&bull; Analytical and creative thinker with excellent time management and problem solving skills.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
